{
  "texts": [
    "Within developing countries, the difficulties posed by the lack of ICT infrastructure in remote areas are compounded by the shortage and high cost of trained legal practitioners in rural and particularly peri-urban areas [25].",
    "To ensure that ICTs can be used by the most marginalized in society to increase access to justice, it is first necessary to increase the overall level of access to the infrastructure.",
    "There are some efforts to improve legal service delivery in rural areas using information communications technology.",
    "Notwithstanding the many and varied applications of ICTs aimed at improving access to legal services for indigent litigants in the developing world, constraints remain which ought not to be underestimated.",
    "Whereas the issue of physical access to the courts might be amenable to ICTs, problems remain concerning the availability of trained legal personnel."
  ]
}